{
  "texts": [
    "The idea of the construction is not too complicated and essentially the same as in [11] and [22].",
    "However, the required notation is fairly involved.",
    "We begin by introducing all of which we shall need.",
    "We use the notation p = p(R).",
    "We also call the principal vertex the left endpoint of R and the point p + re 1 is called the right endpoint of R. We use the notation l(R) and r(R) for the left and the right endpoints of R respectively.For the remainder of this subsection we will consider d ∈ N, d ≥ 2 to be fixed."
  ]
}